SIMPLE: stich
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Stich
<hw>Stich</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <grk>sti`chos</grk>
a row, line, akin to to go, march, E. <ets>sty</ets>, v. i.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>A verse, of whatever measure or number of
feet.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A line in the Scriptures; specifically <fld>(Hebrew
Scriptures)</fld>, one of the rhythmic lines in the poetical books and
passages of the Old Treatment, as written in the oldest Hebrew
manuscripts and in the Revised Version of the English Bible.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A row, line, or rank of trees.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stichic</ent>⟦br⟧
